&lt;li&gt;Manage grid compliance and regulatory obligations across the portfolio, tracking performance standards, registration conditions and commitments, while resolving non-compliances and maintaining clear visibility of risk.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Commercial, F&amp;amp;I, Delivery and Engineering teams to optimise project design, equipment selection and connection strategies, balancing technical risk, cost, schedule and revenue impacts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate modelling priorities with project schedules, connection milestones and engineering delivery, identifying risks early, escalating issues and driving timely cross-functional resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate emerging technology into project outcomes through GPS studies, OEM model development, R2 test plans and commissioning strategies, supporting advanced inverter and grid-forming technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead technical due diligence, component selection and market standards investigations across PCS, control systems, BOP and battery technologies to support scalable, compliant project growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
